· Shift-F1 – this (help) screen
· F1 – tree/command-output view
· F2 – syntax highlighted file contents preview
· F3/Ctrl-E – command history view
· F4 – Ctags index (in Emacs format – TAGS file) browser
· Ctrl-/ – toggle command/execution and search/grep prompts
· F7 – toggle syntax highlighting
· Ctrl-T – copy current item to prompt
· Ctrl-Y – copy current PWD to prompt
· Ctrl-Up/Down – go back and forward in history (of commands or search keywords)
· Ctrl-W – show standard input given on N-C's startup
· Shift-Up – go up one dir (·cd ..·) and run ·$NC_DEFAULT_LS_COMMAND·
· Shift-Down – go back to previous PWD directory
· Shift-Left/Right – move cursor left/right in the current prompt
· Ctrl-Left/Right – move cursor word left/right in prompt
· Ctrl-X – capture save current screen for later retrieval
· Ctrl-Shift-Left/Right – retrieve saved previous/next screen
· F8 – remove the currently shown saved screen from the disk
. <,> – horizontal scroll left,right
